article.headline: Providence 91, Bryant 64
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Marshon Brooks scored 18 points off the bench and Geoff McDermott had a season-high 17 points as Providence beat Bryant 91-64 on Monday night. Sharaud Curry added a season-high 16 points for Providence (8-4), who won by a season-best 27 points in their final non-conference tune-up. Cecil Gresham had a game-high 24 points to lead Bryant (1-9), one of just two Bulldogs to reach double figures. Chris Birrell added seven assists for Bryant, who dropped their seventh straight game. Providence made just one of their first 10 three-pointers, but sunk nine of their next 16 to finish the game 39 percent from behind the arc. The Friars dominated the Bulldogs on the glass, 36 to 24, including 14 offensive rebounds.
